Key Match Events: Budu Zivzivadze earned a caution after seeing his goal disallowed
Zivzivadze doubled Georgia’s lead with a simple tap-in after receiving a pass from Levan Shengelia
Maxime Chanot immediately saw a straight red card after an angry reaction to a VAR decision
Luxembourg thought they had equalised from Gerson Rodrigues’ stunning finish from inside the box, but the goal was disallowed
Post-Match Reflections: Zivzivadze's brace sealed Willy Sagnol’s men a fourth successive unbeaten home game
Willy Sagnol’s men finished third in Group J, more than in their previous six Euro qualifying cycles combined
Miscellaneous Highlights: Georgia booked their place in the Euro 2024 playoff finals with a 2-0 victory at the Boris Paichadze Dinamo Arena over 10-man Luxembourg
Luxembourg bowed out with their heads held high despite Chanot’s actions
The Euro 2024 qualifying campaign represents a minor success in itself for a nation once seen as mere cannon fodder
